article.description: — Tasos Kamateros had a season-high 21 points plus 12 rebounds as South Dakota beat North Dakota 71-58 on Saturday.
article.headline: Kamateros leads South Dakota over North Dakota 71-58
article.linkText: Kamateros leads South Dakota over North Dakota 71-58
article.story: VERMILLION, S.D. -- — Tasos Kamateros had a season-high 21 points plus 12 rebounds as South Dakota beat North Dakota 71-58 on Saturday. Mason Archambault had 12 points for South Dakota (13-8, 6-4 Summit League). Kruz Perrott-Hunt added 12 points. Erik Oliver had 11 points. North Dakota totaled 18 first-half points, a season low for the team. Bentiu Panoam had 19 points for the Fighting Hawks (4-18, 0-9), who have now lost 10 games in a row. Paul Bruns added 17 points. Brady Danielson had eight rebounds. South Dakota also defeated North Dakota 75-68 on Jan. 10. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
